17/03/2011
ANKARA, Turkey -- Police have arrested 20 people in synchronised raids on 40 addresses in the investigation into popular singer Ibrahim Tatlises's shooting, local media reported on Thursday (March 17th). Tatiles was shot in the head Sunday by an unidentified gunman in Istanbul. On Wednesday, he showed clear signs of recovery. Doctors at the Acibadem Maslak Hospital said his survival odds have far improved since he was first admitted. Fans of the singer have surrounded the facility. (Hurriyet, DHA - 17/03/11)
